description: Interested in a career in law? Want to talk to attorneys in different fields? Need advice about law school or how to get an internship? As part of the Vicki Perkins Legal Careers Exploration Program, The BOLD Center will be taking students on a bus trip to New York City to visit Dentons, the world's largest global law firm. Students will have the opportunity to meet with attorneys including Dentons Partner Maria M. Livanos, who represents major financial institutions. She has also been named to Crain’s New York Business’ Notable Women in Law list.  Space is limited so RSVP before March 8th to secure your spot! We will meet at Carpender Hall to take a bus to NYC. A letter to your professors if you need to miss class to attend can be provided.    Dentons Cordially Invites the Women of the Douglass Residential College To Dentons Celebration of International Women’s Day   Agenda 12:00 to 1:00 – Lunch 1:00 to 2:30 – Panel Discussion Regarding Careers in Law 2:30 to 3:00 – Break 3:00 to 4:00 – Dentons International Women’s Day Celebration with Liz Elting, Author and Entrepreneur 4:00 to 4:30 – Presentation of Dentons Excellence Awards 4:30 to 5:00 – Final Thoughts
name: Victoria Perkins Legal Careers Exploration NYC Trip to Dentons Law Firm
organizationName: The BOLD Center at Douglass for Leadership, Career and Personal Development

description: Each year, the S.T.E.A.M. Awards are awarded to members within Rutgers-New Brunswick community who have gone above and beyond to create support for women within S.T.E.A.M. disciplines. The awards are presented to students, faculty and staff at the Dr. Jewel Plummer Cobb S.T.E.A.M. Women’s Empowerment Luncheon. This year’s Luncheon will be held on Monday, March 25, 2024 at 12-1:30pm in the Douglass Student Center, Trayes Hall.   Nominations will be open through March 10. Or, register to join us at the Luncheon by March 20. For additional information on the award and the nomination/RSVP form, please visit: http://steam.rutgers.edu/. *These Prize/these Awards are open to all who meet the applicable criteria, regardless of sex or gender identity.   In addition to nominating members of our community or joining us at the luncheon, please feel free to share this information with your networks. I have attached the graphic to this email. description: Celebrate the end of the academic year by joining Douglass staff, the Voorhees Choir, and fellow students for the annual Sacred Path Ceremony. One of Douglass' oldest traditions, the Sacred Path ceremony recognizes student achievement and fosters Douglass's unique community. Join your fellow Douglass classmates, alumnae, friends, and family as each class is honored with a symbol representing the different class years. After you receive your charm, head to the ceremonial fires on the sacred path to make a wish!  Students should show their pride by wearing their class year colors (first years wear white, sophomores wear pink, juniors wear red, and seniors wear black). Every student will receive a charm, a token representing her class. All Douglass students, family, faculty, and alumnae are welcome! Refreshments will be provided at Ludwig immediately following the ceremony.  *Students in Knowledge & Power will receive 2 points towards their Douglass event requirements*
name: Sacred Path 2024
organizationName: Traditional Events at Douglass Residential College - DRC

We welcome members of any STEM-oriented department to attend the GRIB Conference, present their research, and network with the rest of the Rutgers community!
